Source: Ukrainska Pravda, "Zelenskyy says 1,000-for-1,000 POW swap will take place and confirms truce with Russia on 9-11 May." By Alona Mazurenko, 8 May 2026, 21:31. The article states that Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy said a 1,000-for-1,000 prisoner exchange would take place on 9 May and confirmed an announcement by US President Donald Trump regarding a truce with Russia on 9-11 May. The article identifies its source as Zelenskyy on X (Twitter) and quotes him: "That is why today [8 May - ed.], within the framework of the negotiating process mediated by the American side, we received Russia's agreement to conduct a prisoner exchange in the format of 1,000 for 1,000. A ceasefire regime must also be established on 9, 10 and 11 May." The article adds that Zelenskyy instructed the Ukrainian team to prepare the exchange and thanked President Trump and his team for diplomatic involvement, saying Ukraine expected the United States to ensure that the Russian side fulfilled these agreements. It also quotes Zelenskyy that Red Square was less important than the lives of Ukrainian prisoners who could be brought home. The article notes in background that Trump had announced a three-day truce in the war between Ukraine and Russia.